body_html:
How do I suppress this warning:

WARNING:tensorflow:tf.op_scope(values, name, default_name) is deprecated, use tf.name_scope(name, default_name, values)

This warning originated from recently updated sparse_transpose function in tensorflow.

Here is a testprogram.py file:

import tensorflow as tf

a = tf.SparseTensor(indices=[[0, 0, 0]], values=[1.0+2j], shape=[3, 4, 2])

b = tf.sparse_transpose(a)

print 'Done!'

I tried python -W ignore testprogram.py . However, this warning did not go away.

I also tried export PYTHONWARNINGS="ignore". This did not work either.

Then I tried:

import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')

Did not work. This certainly is one-of-a-kind warming!

My output file is polluted by this warning message. I absolutely want to get rid of it. Please suggest. Thanks!

Edit:

tf.logging.set_verbosity(tf.logging.ERROR)

That solves it.
